# Code of Conduct

## Our Commitment

We are committed to a respectful, inclusive, and harassment-free collaboration
environment for everyone participating in this project.

## Expected Behavior

- Be respectful in communication and technical feedback.
- Assume good intent and discuss ideas, not people.
- Give actionable review comments.
- Accept and provide constructive criticism.

## Unacceptable Behavior

- Harassment, insults, or discriminatory language.
- Personal attacks, threats, or intimidation.
- Publishing private information without explicit permission.
- Repeated disruptive behavior in issues, pull requests, or discussions.

## Enforcement

Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying and enforcing this policy.
They may remove, edit, or reject contributions and communications that violate
this Code of Conduct.

## Reporting

Report incidents privately to project maintainers through a private channel
available in the hosting platform (direct message or private contact method).
Please include links, timestamps, and context so maintainers can investigate.

